<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Kanban Board - basic authentication</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
      <a class="navbar-brand" href="#"> <%= image_tag('logo.svg', size: "30x30", alt: "Kanban Boards", class: 'd-inline-block') %>
        Kanban Boards</a>


      <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNavAltMarkup">
        <span class="navbar-text mr-1">
            Four Demo Apps for Login:
        </span>
        <div class="navbar-nav">
            <a class="nav-link"
               href="https://kanban-1.herokuapp.com/">1: No Login</a>
            <a class="nav-link"
               href="https://kanban-2.herokuapp.com/">2: basic auth
               <span class="sr-only">(current)</span></a>
            <a class="nav-link"
               href="https://kanban-3.herokuapp.com/">3: devise</a>
            <a class="nav-link"
               href="https://kanban-4.herokuapp.com/">4: omniauth</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <span class="navbar-text">
        <% if current_user.nil? %>
          <%= link_to 'login', '/login' %>
            |
          <%= link_to "register", new_user_path %>
        <% else %>
          <%= link_to "logout #{current_user.username}", '/logout' %>
        <% end %>
      </span>
      <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbarNavAltMarkup" aria-controls="navbarNavAltMarkup" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
      </button>
    </nav>

    <div class="container">
      <% flash.each do |key, value| %>
          <div class="alert alert-info mt-1"><strong><%= key %>:</strong> <%= value %></div>
      <% end %>

      <%= yield %>
    </div>
    <footer class="bd-footer text-muted">
      <div class="container">
        <p>This Demo App offers basic authentication with <kbd>has_secure_password</kbd> in the
          user model, and a session controller for login and logout. The id of the current
          user is stored in the session. Rails uses the session-cookie <kbd><%=
        Rails.application.config.session_options[:key] %></kbd> automatically.</p>
        <p>Try logging in as user <kbd>mariam</kbd> with password <kbd>badpassword123</kbd>.</p>
        <p>You can find the source code in branch
          <a href="https://github.com/backend-development/rails-example-kanban-board-login/tree/kanban-2">kanban-2</a> of <a href="https://github.com/backend-development/rails-example-kanban-board-login">the repository</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
